<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12020n"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12020n">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12020n"> 20(n)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> le droit seigneur / celui que Dieu prot&egrave;ge doit / proteger les autres</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">(about Du Guesclin): La chanson populaire de Bretagne l&apos;appelle <mark>&ldquo;le droit seigneur&rdquo;</mark> et lui fait dire cette belle parole: <mark>&ldquo;Celui que Dieu prot&egrave;ge doit prot&eacute;ger les autres.&rdquo;</mark> Lui-m&ecirc;me, dans ses grandes indignations, ne cessait d&apos;appeler Dieu &ldquo;le droiturier&rdquo;. <br><font color="green">[The popular songs of Brittany call him &ldquo;the righteous lord&rdquo; and make him say these beautiful words: &ldquo;He who is protected by God must protect the others.&rdquo; He himself, in his great indignation, did not cease to call God &ldquo;the righteous one.&rdquo;]</font> <small> &Eacute;douard Schur&eacute;, <a name="ESLL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ESLL"><cite title="source">Les Grandes L&eacute;gendes de France</cite></a> (1892) 182</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Fr. He whom God protects, must protect others.</mm> </dd></dl>
